interleave whitespace between recursive let and module bindings (#1990)

* interleave whitespace between recursive let and module bindings

* Inline braces surrounding a Pexp_match as jsx child.

* Consistent with Prettier
* Wastes less whitespace

Before:
```reason
<div>
  {
    switch (color) {
    | Black => ReasonReact.string("black")
    | Red => ReasonReact.string("red")
    }
  }
</div>;
```

```reason
<div>
  {switch (color) {
   | Black => ReasonReact.string("black")
   | Red => ReasonReact.string("red")
   }}
</div>;
```

* Cleanup unused code

* fix esy build

Support single line comments of the form `// comment` (#2254)

* Add support for single line comments of the form //

* Fix edge case where // inside a sequence wrapped in braces didn't break.

```reason
let x = {
  //
};
```

If the { }-sequence didn't break we would get parse error:

```reason
let x = { // };
```

Inline braces surrounding a Pexp_match as jsx child. (#2208)

* Consistent with Prettier
* Wastes less whitespace

Before:
```reason
<div>
  {
    switch (color) {
    | Black => ReasonReact.string("black")
    | Red => ReasonReact.string("red")
    }
  }
</div>;
```

```reason
<div>
  {switch (color) {
   | Black => ReasonReact.string("black")
   | Red => ReasonReact.string("red")
   }}
</div>;
```

Supreme printing of anonymous functions as props in jsx. (#2198)

* Supreme printing of anonymous functions as props in jsx.

BEFORE:
<div
  onClick={
    event => {
      Js.log(event);
      handleChange(event);
    }
  }
/>;

AFTER:
<div
  onClick={event => {             ----> inline the arguments
    Js.log(event);
    handleChange(event);
  }}                             ----> brace hugging
/>;

* Add extra tests with named args and take care of constraint expressions

* Format single arguments with a constraint on the Pexp_fun correct.

* Add more tests

Improve printing of breaking layout with single fastpipe. (#2193)

Before:
reactClass
->setNavigationOptions(
    NavigationOptions.t(~title="Title", ~gesturesEnabled=false, ()),
  );

After:
reactClass->setNavigationOptions(
  NavigationOptions.t(~title="Title", ~gesturesEnabled=false, ()),
);

Recover jsx component near arrow of pattern match. (#2060)

switch(foo) {
  | `Variant =><Component />
};

`=><` isn't an infix operator in this context.

Print newline after doc comments before attributes (#1869)

* newline between doc comment and attr on external

Forces a line break following doc comments before the first
non-comment attribute on a BuckleScript external.

Before:

/** doc comment */ [@bs.send] external url : t => string = "";

/**
 * Short multiline doc comment
 */ [@bs.send]
external url : t => string = "";

After:

/** doc comment */
[@bs.send]
external url : t => string = "";

/**
 * Short multiline doc comment
 */
[@bs.send]
external url : t => string = "";

* Add tests for doc comments on type and let

* Use partitionAttributes now that it handles docs

Doc comments were previously disabled.

Fix inconsistent printing of opening extension expressions. (#1979)

The `open` expr `open Syntax` contains an extension as child expression.
This is a "sequency" expression and should not be formatted with the
open syntax sugar.

The following should be formatted as is:

let work = () => {
  open Syntax;
  let%bind name = x;
  name;
};

Fix parsing/lexing of jsx inside a list under open sugar. (#1894)

Allow:
  Module.[<Component />];

More idiomatic printing of uncurried function
signatures return uncurried functions.

type f = (int, . int) => unit;

prints as

type f = int => (. int) => unit;

Fix the format idempotency of open type declarations

e.g.

  type a = b = ..;

was being formatted as

  type a = .. = b;

Fix subtle jsx parsing issues.

let x =[|<div />|];
let x=<div />;
let y = (<div />, <div />);
<Foo bar=<Baz /> />;
foo#=<bar />;
<div asd=1></div>;

Implement paren hugging for patterns. (#1551)

Example:
switch x {
| Some({
    a,
    b,
  }) => ...
}

Notice how ({ and }) stick together

Bump topkg requirements (#1544)

@let-def's #1541 seems to require a newer version of topkg that provides
a `-r` flag

Stick parens of function or (poly)variant application together with (#1516)

outer structure wrapping of the expr param when there's a single param.

Example:
MyConstructor({x: reallyLong, y: anotherReallyLongThing});

->
MyConstructor({
  x: reallyLong,
  y: anotherReallyLongThing
});

Notice how ({ and }) stick together

Support pretty printing extensions in include statement. (#1035)

This get pretty printed correct now:
```
include
  [%matchenv
    switch (GL_BACKEND) {
      | "native" => Reglnative.Opengl
      | "web" => Reglweb.Webgl
    }
    ];
```

More clarifying examples for "type parameters" (#970)

It is not obvious that the list can have any amounts of elements with `list string`.

```reason
type listOfStrings = list string;
let lst : listOfStrings = ["hi", "bye"];
let lst2 : listOfStrings = ["oh", "no", "not, "you", "again"];

```

This is an easy one to trip over. I suggest adding a second example to clarify it.

```reason
type result 'a 'b =
  | Ok 'a
  | Error 'b;
let r : result string int = Ok "here is the result";
let r2 : result string int = Error 500;

Fix overeager punning in record types (#962). (#964)

* Fix overeager punning in record types (#962).

module Foo = {
  type bar = {foo: Baz.foo};
};

should not become

module Foo = {
  type bar = {foo};
};

The latter will look for a `type foo` inside `module Foo`,
which isn't what we want. When determining if a record row should
be punned, there is now a check in place which takes types with longer identifiers - `Baz.foo` - into account.

* Favor pattern matching over flattening when checking if the longident contains a dot

Record field type punning (#926)

* Implement field type punning in parser & printer + update docs

* Fix bug: don't pun parameterized record types.

type componentDescription 'props = {
  tag: tag 'props,
  layout: LayoutSupport.LayoutTypes.node,
  instantiatedChildren: list component
};

shouldn't be printed as

type componentDescription 'props = {
  tag,
  layout: LayoutSupport.LayoutTypes.node,
  instantiatedChildren: list component
};

The latter results in a bug,
the type constructor tag expects 1 argument.

[Reason] Support last row in record type definitions.

Summary: No place in the AST records the locations of the open/close
braces, but we can come up with a heuristic that captures the vast
majority of use cases.

If you write code like the following, (either in OCaml, or Reason) your
comments will be preserved in their correct locations.

```
/* Before type t */
type t = {
  /* Before x */
  x: int,  /* after x */
  /* Before y */
  y: int  /* after y */
  /* Final row */
};
```

Watch out for the following common mistake:

```
type t = {
  /* Before x */
  x: int,  /* after x */
  /* Before y */
  y: int  /* after y */ };

The closing brace position makes `y` not be at the *end* of the line, so
it won't be preserved as an end of line comment.

```

